// - ADXL345 @ 12.5 Hz (I2C, low-power mode), FIFO STREAM + polling (no INT pin)
// - GPS: wake -> wait -> log 1 row -> standby (every 3 minutes, UBX RXM-PMREQ standby/wake)
// - BLE: passive scan to /BLE.CSV with per-window de-dup (MAC+RSSI)
// - Unified event ring buffer sized at runtime from allocatable heap after init
//   • Normal flush at 85% of that capacity; emergency at 87.25%
//   • Event-driven flush hints set on each push; SD writes only from loop() (low power)
// - Disciplined UTC clock + 64-bit uptime; events stamped at CAPTURE time
// - USB command: "MSC ON" / "MSC OFF" to expose/hide SD as a USB drive
//
// Serial Monitor: 115200

